OL,3,CPraise and criticism for Drakeford in
OL,4,CCovid inquiry report
OL,6,FBut it said none of the four
OL,7,Fgovernments gave enough consideration
OL,8,Fto the possibility of a second wave,
OL,9,Fmeaning there was very little
OL,10,Fcontingency planning in place.
OL,12,FIt added that the Welsh Government
OL,13,Fintroduced restrictions too late when
OL,14,Ffaced with rising cases in autumn
OL,15,F2020, and they were not in place for
OL,16,Flong enough or were too weak.
